National Security Advisor Jake Sullivan spoke with National Security Advisor Ajit Doval to express sympathy for India's recent surge in COVID-19 cases. They affirmed the solidarity between the two countries and agreed to continue fighting the pandemic together. The United States will provide assistance to India, including raw materials for vaccine production, therapeutics, diagnostic test kits, ventilators, PPE, and oxygen supplies. The U.S. will also support the expansion of vaccine manufacturing capability in India and deploy a team of public health advisors. The two advisors agreed to stay in close contact in the coming days.